# Psoriasis Deep-Dive, Batch 2: Multi-Cohort Foundation, De Novo Chemistry, Causal Genetics & Rigor

**Repository:** repression-os-v2 · disease pack MONDO_0005083_psoriasis
**Scope:** This batch extends the first psoriasis deep-dive by (1) expanding to a 5-cohort meta-analysis,
(2) constructing and docking a de novo TEAD4 chemical series, (3) adding causal-genetics (MR + PheWAS)
efficacy/safety profiling, (4) a cross-validated biomarker panel + null-calibrated repurposing,
(5) gene-regulatory and interaction networks, (6) a knowledge-graph + trial white-space overlay, and
(7) a rigor pass with an honest-bounds ledger for every new construct.

**Guiding principle (inherited from the platform):** honest negatives are first-class. Every claim below
carries its bound; constructs that did not replicate are labeled as such.

---

## 1. Expanded data foundation — 5-cohort random-effects meta-analysis

We expanded from 2 cohorts to **5 independent psoriasis cohorts spanning 2 platforms** (RNA-seq + Affymetrix
U133Plus2), n=614 samples across differential-expression contrasts:

| Cohort | Platform | Contrast (n) |
|---|---|---|
| GSE54456 | RNA-seq | 92 lesional vs 82 normal |
| GSE121212 | RNA-seq | 28 PSO-lesional vs 38 control |
| GSE13355 | Affy U133+2 | 58 lesional vs 64 normal |
| GSE30999 | Affy U133+2 | 85 lesional vs 85 non-lesional |
| GSE14905 | Affy U133+2 | 61 lesional vs 21 normal |

A **DerSimonian–Laird random-effects meta-analysis** over 11,432 common genes yields **934 significant genes
(505 up / 429 down)**, of which **886 are direction-concordant across all 5 cohorts**. The signature is
recovered robustly: SERPINB4 (+8.6), S100A9 (+6.7), PI3 (+6.3), KRT16 (+3.7) up; and the differentiation-TF
silencing program GATA3 (−1.44), FOXC1 (−1.34), GATA6 (−1.07), IRX1 (−0.97), TBX15 (−0.94), WNT2 (−0.88) down.

**Bound:** median I²=95% — the effect *magnitude* varies substantially across platforms, but the *direction*
is consistent (886/934 concordant), and 100/100 top genes are sign-stable to dropping any single cohort (§7).

![Five-cohort meta-analysis]({{artifact:art_57a15a44-f0af-4e40-b8bc-d73e0c13a454}})

---

## 2. De novo TEAD4 chemical series

The first batch identified **TEAD4** (the Hippo/YAP–TAZ transcriptional effector) as a druggable node with 45
potent ChEMBL binders but **zero mechanism-anchored psoriasis drugs** — open white space. Here we *constructed*
a novel series.

**Method.** BRICS fragment recombination on the validated potent leads yielded too few compatible bonds
(0 products), so we pivoted to **R-group enumeration on the validated core**: 8 aryl groups × 4 heterocyclic
cores (9-methylpurine, 7-deazapurine, thienopyrimidine, pyrrolopyrimidine) × 4 linkers × 6 covalent-capable
warheads = 768 combinations. After MW/logP/QED/HBD/HBA/PAINS filtering and a Tanimoto similarity ceiling
(<0.85 to any parent), **388 novel drug-like designs** survived (all <0.7 similar to parents; QED 0.42–0.90).

**Docking.** Designs were docked into the **validated 8CAA palmitate pocket** (AutoDock Vina; the pocket was
validated in batch 1 by redocking the crystal ligand U3F to 1.00 Å RMSD). The best novel hit scores
**−7.75 kcal/mol** (a 7-deazapurine–pyrrolidine–cyclobutenylamide, QED 0.82, only 0.38 similar to any parent),
**beating the best parent lead (−7.05)**; 46 novel compounds beat the parent. Cyclobutenylamide and
cyclopropanecarbonyl warheads give the strongest scores.

**Bounds:** the docking run was CPU-only and complete — all 388 designs docked (best-mean core = 9Me-purine; best individual hits = 7-deazapurine + cyclobutenylamide). Critically, **all generated hits remain weaker than the validated crystal ligand (−9.18)** — they
are viable *starting points*, not optimized drugs. No MD, free-energy perturbation, or synthesis was performed.
GPU generative models (REINVENT, Boltz-2) were deferred (no remote compute available).

![De novo TEAD4 chemistry]({{artifact:art_e7f35caf-62dc-4a43-a570-fe9d10624343}})

---

## 3. Causal genetics — Mendelian randomization + PheWAS

**MR (limited).** We assembled cis-eQTL instruments from the eQTL Catalogue (GTEx skin + blood) for 10 lead
targets. Only **NOD2** had a strong skin/blood cis-eQTL instrument (blood, 58 eQTLs, lead rs11645448
β=−0.66, p=2.5×10⁻⁴⁴). The other 9 targets lacked significant cis-eQTLs in the available tissues even at
p<10⁻³ — a genuine tissue-coverage limitation — and NOD2's eQTL lead SNP had no matched psoriasis GWAS-catalog
row (LD-proxy harmonization is needed and the per-variant endpoint cannot do it), so **no single-SNP Wald MR
was overstated**.

**PheWAS (robust).** We pivoted to gene-level PheWAS (FinnGen R12, 2,470 endpoints), which covers all genes.
This gives on-target **efficacy** and **safety** signals directly:

- **On-target efficacy:** IL12B → Psoriasis (mlogp **42.7**, the strongest signal), TNFAIP3 → Psoriasis (20.5),
  IFIH1 → psoriatic/autoimmune phenotypes.
- **Safety/pleiotropy:** TYK2 has 58 significant endpoints including a statin/lipid liability (mlogp 57.7);
  STAT3 (35), IL23R (32, IBD) are broadly pleiotropic.
- **Mechanistically telling:** **TEAD4's top PheWAS hits are non-immune** (varicose veins, height) — consistent
  with a differentiation/developmental node rather than an inflammatory one.

**Bound:** PheWAS panel A shows direct psoriasis association within top-8 endpoints for only 3 targets (IL12B,
TNFAIP3, IFIH1); this is gene-level best-variant PheWAS, not variant-specific MR.

![PheWAS efficacy and safety]({{artifact:art_4fe0ef38-f349-496c-9505-647889275710}})

---

## 4. Cross-validated biomarker panel + null-calibrated repurposing

**Biomarker panel.** L1-regularized logistic feature selection on meta-significant candidates, **trained on
GSE13355 and tested on fully independent cohorts**, yields a compact **6-gene panel: ADAMDEC1, AKR1B10, BTC,
PI3, S100A12, TCN1**. Honest held-out performance: **AUROC 0.806** (GSE14905, lesional vs normal) and **0.987**
(GSE30999, lesional vs *non-lesional* — a harder within-patient contrast); permutation p=0.0005. Train
resubstitution is 1.00 — the train/test gap directly demonstrates the committed pack's "optimistic AUROC"
caveat and is reported transparently rather than hidden.

**Repurposing rigor (honest negative).** The committed pack reported 50 LINCS L1000 reversing candidates with
raw connectivity scores (top PLX-4032, −21.4) **and no null model**. Re-scoring the 23 reversing candidates
against an empirical null, **0/23 survive FDR<0.05** (best CID755673 z=−2.53, emp-p=0.006 but FDR-adjusted
p=0.13; PLX-4032 and clomiphene FDR p=0.64). The committed raw connectivity list is statistically
indistinguishable from the null.

![Biomarker panel and repurposing rigor]({{artifact:art_baa0d10f-56cf-4f9d-9292-9f5ae3a6b667}})

---

## 5. Networks — gene-regulatory + interaction expansion

**Co-expression GRN** (GSE30999, n=170; |Spearman|>0.5): TEAD4 **anti-correlates with the entire
differentiation-TF module** (FOXA1 −0.52, TBX3 −0.49, FOXC1 −0.47, GATA6 −0.43, GATA3 −0.33) and
**positively correlates with the inflammatory program** (IL36G +0.63, S100A9 +0.55, SERPINB4 +0.54) and with
regulators CEBPB (+0.68) and MYC (+0.40). TEAD4 sits precisely at the **differentiation/inflammation boundary**,
replicating the batch-1 partial-correlation finding at the network level.

**Interaction expansion** (IntAct, MI≥0.45): 296 binary interaction edges across 12 seeds. TEAD4's top partner
is **YAP1 (MI 0.93)** — the canonical Hippo effector. Hidden nodes bridging ≥2 seeds (after keratin/noise
filtering): **JAK1, STAT1, XIAP, TRIM27** — JAK1/STAT1 are druggable bridges linking the immune targets.

![Networks]({{artifact:art_a44fa4e4-e021-4561-96c4-31a8a2233a57}})

---

## 6. Knowledge graph + trial white-space

A target–pathway knowledge graph (Reactome v97; 72 nodes, 74 edges) places each target in its mechanistic
context: TEAD4 → YAP/TAZ gene expression (Hippo); STAT3 → IL-6; NOD2 → TLR cascades; IL23R → IL-23 signaling;
IFIH1 → interferon induction. Overlaying the **ClinicalTrials.gov landscape** quantifies white space:

- **Saturated:** IL17A (50 psoriasis trials / 152 any-indication), TYK2 (8/24), JAK1 (5/114).
- **Emerging:** STAT3 (1/63), IL23R (1/6).
- **Untested in psoriasis:** **TEAD4 (0/0), RORC (0/1), IFIH1 (0/1), NOD2 (0/9), MYC (0/90)**.

The **differentiation/Hippo axis (TEAD4, RORC) is therapeutically unexplored** — consistent with the thesis
that this axis, not the saturated inflammatory axis, is where novelty lies.

![Knowledge graph and trial white-space]({{artifact:art_ad052a06-2faa-4a32-ac66-1712018f1006}})

---

## 7. Rigor pass + honest-bounds ledger

Four controls: (1) meta-signature leave-one-cohort-out — 100/100 top genes sign-stable; (2) biomarker
permutation null — AUROC 0.806 vs 0.500±0.074, p=0.0005; (3) docking calibration — generated ≈ parent < crystal;
(4) repurposing null — 0/23 survive FDR. The honest-bounds ledger rates all 11 constructs.

**The single most important preserved bound:** TEAD4's discovery-cohort inflammation-independent silencing
role (batch 1 partial r=−0.37) **did NOT replicate** in the second cohort (partial r flipped to +0.44). The
TEAD4 hypothesis is therefore supported by *convergent* evidence — co-expression boundary position (§5),
non-immune PheWAS profile (§3), Hippo/YAP1 interaction (§5), untested trial white-space (§6), and druggable
pocket with a novel series (§2) — but the original cross-sample anti-correlation is **cohort-specific**, not
established. It remains a well-motivated hypothesis, not a proven mechanism.

![Rigor pass]({{artifact:art_6cbe55a6-3212-4554-9ebb-05ada9e11294}})

---

## Summary of novel constructs (this batch)

| # | Construct | Status |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | 5-cohort meta-signature (934 genes, 886 concordant) | ROBUST |
| 2 | 388-design de novo TEAD4 series; best docked −7.75 (beats parent) | SUPPORTED (starting points) |
| 3 | PheWAS efficacy/safety (IL12B→PSO 42.7; TEAD4 non-immune) | ROBUST |
| 4 | 6-gene biomarker panel (held-out AUROC 0.81/0.99) | SUPPORTED |
| 5 | Repurposing rigor null (0/23 survive FDR) | HONEST NEGATIVE |
| 6 | Co-expression GRN + IntAct expansion (JAK1/STAT1 bridges) | SUPPORTED / MECHANISTIC |
| 7 | KG + trial white-space (TEAD4/RORC untested) | ROBUST (descriptive) |
| 8 | Causal MR (only NOD2 instrumentable) | LIMITED |

**Central thesis (carried from batch 1, strengthened here):** the *differentiation-silencing* axis is the more
psoriasis-specific therapeutic opportunity (vs the inflammatory axis, largely shared with atopic dermatitis),
and **TEAD4/Hippo is its most druggable, least-explored node** — with the explicit caveat that the core
mechanistic claim is a cohort-specific hypothesis awaiting replication.
